args: No, sir. No sign of him.
This is completely insane—we don't even\nKNOW each other! I just forced him into\ngoing on a date he didn't even want!
Not so insane after all, it seems.
I trust you've come with the\nitem we discussed?
I ain't bringin' you a head.
The master I serve values\nvirtue above all else.
We ain't the sort of scumbags who'd sell\neach other out to protect our own honor.
And yet, are you not selling out this poor\ngirl for the sake of your master's ＂honor＂?
Ha ha! Explain, if you would.
Knowing what's right and choosin'\notherwise makes you a coward—\nand I ain't no coward.
So I'm gonna protect my master's honor\nAND save Helena! Hyaaahhhh!
Hold on tight, okay? I ain't gonna drop you.
Apologies for takin' the liberty, but I'm\ngonna have to carry you for a spell.\nNow let's make tracks while we can!
I'm so sorry, Addis. This is all my fault!
Less talk, more hangin' on, yeah?
Hmph. There's no way they'd\nlet us escape this easily...
Stay behind me and keep\nyour back to this tree.
Addis, I don't know how to use a blade!
Stick the pointy end in the bad guy.
I'm gonna do what I can to keep 'em\naway from you. If this goes well,\nyou won't have to stab nobody.
Yep—and also I got a damn good idea\nhow to use the thing. Haaaaah!
Ninjas are supposed to stay quiet, pal—\nbut thanks for pointin' yourself out! Haaah!
(But why is my heart still pounding?\nDid I miss one somewhere?)
Nnngh... A-Addis, you have to run!

Allow me to introduce you to the secret
ninja technique of the Spider Puppet.
Those I ensnare with my silken strands
of mana have no hope of escape.
The more you pull against the strings,\nthe more you rend your own flesh.\nNow dance, my puppet! Dance!
So you're gonna make Helena do your\nfightin' while you hide like a whipped cur?
You really are the lowliest of cowards!
Cowardice holds no meaning to those who\nlive in shadow. Oh, and I must thank you\nfor kindly lending the woman your blade!
Run and she dies! You know full well\nwe cannot permit you to survive\nnow that you know our plans.
(Damn it, where is this creep?\nI can't sense him anywhere!)
I...I won't let you make me do this!\nHRRRAAAAAAAAAGH!
Have you gone mad, you fool woman?!\nIf you struggle against these strings,\nthey'll rend your limbs from your body!
Wait. Look at those leaves fall...\nHe's under that tree! Haaaaaaah!
Stay still—your arms are all torn up.
Such wounds are a small price to pay\nfor protecting you, my dear Addis...
I can't even imagine how much pain\nyou went through to do this...
Yet how could I not when faced with the\nthought of him harming the man I love?
Love makes people stronger.\nI understand that now.
Thank you, Helena. I owe you one.\nNow let's get you patched up...
